OE PROGRAM 7

Application Load Balancer

Aim
To configure Application Load Balancer.

Step 1 Open EC2

1. Open EC2 Dashboard.
2. Open Load Balancers from left panel.

Step 2 Create Load Balancer

1. Click Create Load Balancer.
2. Select Application Load Balancer.
3. Enter name.
4. Select VPC.
5. Select public subnets.

Step 3 Create Target Group

1. Click Create Target Group.
2. Select EC2 instances.
3. Register instances.

Step 4 Finish Setup

1. Attach target group.
2. Create load balancer.
3. Copy DNS URL.
4. Test in browser.

Result
Application Load Balancer configured successfully.

